The paper discusses a method to improve the sample efficiency of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of demonstrations and curriculum learning, which are common techniques in the subfields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also analyzes the effectiveness of the proposed method in a complex four-player zero-sum game, which falls under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the use of analytical characterization, which is a common technique in the subfield of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
